to the editor re how bright the sky editorial aug 24 millions of us are now deprived of any view of the breathtaking night sky and its awesome milky way but we need n't lose this treasure permanently we can redesign lighting intelligently to keep lighting on its intended target it 's useless to spill light onto neighbors and into the sky we should note the innumerable examples of profligate lighting and encourage common sense redesign for example a prison near my virginia farm sets the sky ablaze for miles around using intense lighting that trespasses on neighbors and ruins the pristine nighttime beauty of the estaline valley terrorizing inmates seems less useful than monitoring them effectively modern video cameras work just fine in faint light kurt w riegel columbia md aug 24 2001 the writer an astronomer teaches environmental engineering at johns hopkins university

